{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W7uwiCp2PEWeaBgMs8nwP8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nHere are the key TypeScript compiler options for the RNG Utopia project:\n\n**Key Compiler Options:**\n\n| Option | Value | Notes |\n|--------|-------|-------|\n| **target** | ES2022 | Compiles to ES2022 standard |\n| **module** | ESNext | Uses ESNext module format (modern ES modules) |\n| **moduleResolution** | bundler | Uses bundler-friendly resolution (supports subpath exports, package.json imports) |\n| **lib** | ES2022 | Provides ES2022 standard library types |\n\n**ESM-Related Settings:**\n- **esModuleInterop**: `true` — Allows CommonJS modules to interoperate with ES modules\n- **isolatedModules**: `true` — Ensures each file can be safely transpiled independently\n- **resolveJsonModule**: `true` — Allows importing JSON files as modules\n- **declaration**: `true` — Generates `.d.ts` files for type definitions\n- **declarationMap**: `true` — Generates source maps for declarations\n\n**Other Notable Strict Settings:**\n- **strict**: `true` — Enables all strict type-checking options\n- **strictNullChecks**: `true` — Strict null/undefined checking\n- **noUnusedLocals** / **noUnusedParameters**: `true` — Errors on unused code\n- **noUncheckedIndexedAccess**: `true` — Strict indexed access safety\n- **forceConsistentCasingInFileNames**: `true` — Case-sensitive file resolution\n\nThis configuration is **fully ESM-native** with a modern ES2022 target, suitable for Node 24+ which natively supports top-level await and ES modules without the `--experimental-modules` flag."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a852a183c110a903d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32162\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 7591</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"43f990b3-3b80-4952-b266-f65de083e062","uuid":"e5a51062-aa02-4645-900d-547b1786c938","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/config/tsconfig.node.json and tell me the key compiler options especially: module, moduleResolution, target, and any other ESM-related settings.","agentId":"a852a183c110a903d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nHere are the key TypeScript compiler options for the RNG Utopia project:\n\n**Key Compiler Options:**\n\n| Option | Value | Notes |\n|--------|-------|-------|\n| **target** | ES2022 | Compiles to ES2022 standard |\n| **module** | ESNext | Uses ESNext module format (modern ES modules) |\n| **moduleResolution** | bundler | Uses bundler-friendly resolution (supports subpath exports, package.json imports) |\n| **lib** | ES2022 | Provides ES2022 standard library types |\n\n**ESM-Related Settings:**\n- **esModuleInterop**: `true` — Allows CommonJS modules to interoperate with ES modules\n- **isolatedModules**: `true` — Ensures each file can be safely transpiled independently\n- **resolveJsonModule**: `true` — Allows importing JSON files as modules\n- **declaration**: `true` — Generates `.d.ts` files for type definitions\n- **declarationMap**: `true` — Generates source maps for declarations\n\n**Other Notable Strict Settings:**\n- **strict**: `true` — Enables all strict type-checking options\n- **strictNullChecks**: `true` — Strict null/undefined checking\n- **noUnusedLocals** / **noUnusedParameters**: `true` — Errors on unused code\n- **noUncheckedIndexedAccess**: `true` — Strict indexed access safety\n- **forceConsistentCasingInFileNames**: `true` — Case-sensitive file resolution\n\nThis configuration is **fully ESM-native** with a modern ES2022 target, suitable for Node 24+ which natively supports top-level await and ES modules without the `--experimental-modules` flag."}],"totalDurationMs":7591,"totalTokens":32162,"totalToolUseCount":2,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":31291,"output_tokens":412,"server_tool_use":{"web